Reading files


Reading files

# To read any text file (compressed / uncompressed into an RDD)

rdd = sc.textFile(&quot;…path&quot;)

#To read any sequence file (compressed / uncompressed into an RDD)

rdd = sc.sequenceFile(&quot;…path&quot;)

#To read a parquet file (compressed/uncompressed):

df = sqlContext.read.parquet(&quot;…path&quot;)

#To read a orc file (compressed/uncompressed):

df = sqlContext.read.orc(&quot;…path&quot;)

#To read a json file (compressed/uncompressed):

df = sqlContext.read.json(&quot;…path&quot;)

#To read a text file (compressed/uncompressed) to a data frame:

df = sqlContext.read.text(&quot;…path&quot;)

#To read an avro file (compressed/uncompressed):

df = sqlContext.load(&quot;…path&quot;,&quot;com.databricks.spark.avro&quot;)

 or

import com.databricks.spark.avro.\_;

df = sqlContext.read.avro(&quot;…path&quot;);

### Writing files

#To write an RDD into text file to HDFS. By default compressionClassCodec=None. This means no compression.

Available codecs: BZip2Codec or GzipCodec or SnappyCodec.

rdd.saveAsTextFile(&quot;…path&quot;, classOf[org.apache.hadoop.io.compress.SnappyCodec])

#To write an RDD into a sequence file:

rdd.saveAsSequenceFile(&quot;…path&quot;, Some(classOf[org.apache.hadoop.io.compress.GzipCodec]))

#save DF with options:

df.write.format(&quot;csv&quot;).mode(&quot;overwrite&quot;).option(&quot;sep&quot;, &quot;#&quot;)

.partitionBy(&quot;column\_name&quot;).save(&quot;/tmp/output/csv&quot;)

#To write data frame in parquet, avro, json, orc with/without compression (default: snappy):

#1. Set the parquet compression. In place of &quot;gzip&quot;, use &quot;snappy&quot;, &quot;lzo&quot;, &quot;uncompressed&quot; or &quot;gzip&quot;

sqlContext.setConf(&quot;spark.sql.parquet.compression.codec&quot;,&quot;gzip&quot;)

#2. Write the file now in parquet format. mode can be &quot;overwrite&quot; or &quot;append&quot; or &quot;error&quot;

df.write.parquet(&quot;…path&quot;, mode=&quot;overwrite&quot;))

#1. Set avro compression # Can be &quot;snappy&quot;, &quot;deflate&quot; or &quot;uncompressed&quot;

sqlContext.setConf(&quot;spark.sql.avro.compression.codec&quot;,&quot;snappy&quot;)

#2. Write in avro format now #

df.format(&#39;com.databricks.spark.avro&#39;).save(&quot;…path&quot;)

import com.databricks.spark.avro.\_;
df.write.avro(&quot;…path&quot;);

#I think by default the data is compressed by snappy format for ORC

df.write.orc(&quot;…path&quot;)

#Write the JSON file without compression

df.toJSON.saveAsTextFile(&quot;…path&quot;)

# Write the JSON file with compression

df.toJSON.saveAsTextFile(&quot;…path&quot;, classOf[org.apache.hadoop.io.compress.GzipCodec])

df.write.option(&quot;compression&quot;, &quot;gzip&quot;).json(&quot;…path&quot;) // for Spark 2

get # of partitions:

df.rdd.getNumPartitions

#Write RDD and DF with desired number of partitions ##

# - For RDD:

rdd.coalesce(2).saveAsTextFile(&quot;…path&quot;)

# - For DF:

df.rdd.coalesce(2).toDF()

 or

val singlePartitionDF = df.coalesce(1)

### Transformation

# RDD to DF

var orders\_rdd=sc.textFile(&quot;/user/training/data/retail\_db/orders&quot;)

var orders\_df=orders\_rdd.map(x =\&gt;

 { var d = x.split(&quot;,&quot;);

   (d(0).toInt,d(1),d(2).toInt,d(3))

 }).toDF(&quot;order\_id&quot;,&quot;order\_date&quot;,&quot;order\_customer\_id&quot;,&quot;order\_status&quot;)

# Join DF, optional left join

var order\_joined = orders\_df.join(order\_items\_df,orders\_df(&quot;order\_id&quot;) === order\_items\_df(&quot;order\_item\_order\_id&quot;), &quot;left&quot;)

### Dealing with Hive

Create Hive context (in Spark 2.x it&#39;s not needed as it is merged into spark.sqlContext)

var hc = new org.apache.spark.sql.hive.HiveContext(sc)

# view registered SQL views:

spark.catalog.listTables.show

# **multi** -line SQL using triple quotes:

spark.sql(&quot;&quot;&quot;select \* from m&quot;&quot;&quot;)

# save DF as hive table in Spark (deprecated)

someDF.registerTempTable(&quot;temptablename&quot;)

sqlContext.sql(&quot;select \* from temptablename&quot;).show

val someDF=sqlContext.sql(&quot;select \* from temptablename&quot;)

val options = Map(&quot;path&quot; -\&gt; hiveTablePath) //optional hive path

someDF.write.mode(&quot;overwrite&quot;).options(options).saveAsTable(&quot;dbname.hiveTable&quot;)

)

### Problem 5

Import orders table from mysql (db: retail\_db , user : retail\_user , password : xxxx)

Read above hdfs data

Consider orders only in &quot;COMPLETE&quot; status and order id between 1000 and 50000 (1001 to 49999)

Save the output (only 2 columns orderid and orderstatus) in parquet format with gzip compression in location /user/cloudera/problem5-parquet-gzip/

sqoop import
--connect jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/retail\_db
--username retail\_dba
--password cloudera
--table orders
--as-avrodatafile
--compress
--compression-codec snappy
--target-dir /user/cloudera/problem5-avro-snappy/

val ordersDF= sqlContext.read.format(&quot;com.databricks.spark.avro&quot;).load(&quot;/user/cloudera/problem5-avro-snappy&quot;)
ordersDF.registerTempTable(&quot;orders&quot;)
val result = sqlContext.sql(&quot;select order\_id,order\_status from orders where order\_status like &#39;COMPLETE&#39; and order\_id \&gt; 1000 and order\_id \&lt; 50000&quot;)
// alternative:
val result = ordersDF.filter(&quot;order\_id \&gt;1000 and order\_id\&lt;50000 and order\_status like &#39;COMPLETE&#39;&quot;).select(&quot;order\_id&quot;,&quot;order\_status&quot;)

sqlContext.setConf(&quot;spark.sql.parquet.compression.codec&quot;,&quot;gzip&quot;)
result.coalesce(2).write.parquet(&quot;/user/cloudera/problem5-parquet-gzip&quot;)

// 3. Rank products within department by price and order by department asc and rank desc

var hiveResult = hc.sql(

&quot;select d.department\_id, p.product\_id, p.product\_name, p.product\_price,

rank() over (partition by d.department\_id order by p.product\_price) as product\_price\_rank,

dense\_rank() over (partition by d.department\_id order by p.product\_price) as product\_dense\_price\_rank

from products p inner join categories c on c.category\_id = p.product\_category\_id  inner join departments d on c.category\_department\_id = d.department\_id  order by d.department\_id, product\_price\_rank desc, product\_dense\_price\_rank &quot;);

// 4. Find top 10 customers with most unique product purchases. If more than one customer has the same number of product purchases, then the customer with the lowest customer\_id will take precedence

var hiveResult2 = hc.sql(&quot;select c.customer\_id, c.customer\_fname, count(distinct(oi.order\_item\_product\_id)) unique\_products

from customers c inner join orders o on o.order\_customer\_id = c.customer\_id  inner join order\_items oi on o.order\_id = oi.order\_item\_order\_id

group by c.customer\_id, c.customer\_fname

order by unique\_products desc, c.customer\_id limit 10&quot;)

// 5. On dataset from step 3, apply filter such that only products less than 100 are extracted

hiveResult.registerTempTable(&quot;product\_rank\_result\_temp&quot;);

hc.sql(&quot;select \* from product\_rank\_result\_temp where product\_price \&lt; 100&quot;).show();

// 6. On dataset from step 4, extract details of products purchased by top 10 customers which are priced at less than 100 USD per unit

var topCustomers = hc.sql(&quot;select c.customer\_id, c.customer\_fname, count(distinct(oi.order\_item\_product\_id)) unique\_products

from customers c inner join orders o on o.order\_customer\_id = c.customer\_id  inner join order\_items oi on o.order\_id = oi.order\_item\_order\_id

group by c.customer\_id, c.customer\_fname

order by unique\_products desc, c.customer\_id limit 10&quot;);

topCustomers.registerTempTable(&quot;top\_cust&quot;);

var topProducts = hc.sql(&quot;select distinct p.\* from products p inner join order\_items oi on oi.order\_item\_product\_id = p.product\_id inner join orders o on o.order\_id = oi.order\_item\_order\_id inner join top\_cust tc on o.order\_customer\_id = tc.customer\_id where p.product\_price \&lt; 100&quot;);

// Store the result of 5 and 6 in new meta store tables within hive

hc.sql(&quot;create table problem6.product\_rank\_result as select \* from product\_rank\_result\_temp where product\_price \&lt; 100&quot;);

hc.sql(&quot;create table problem6.top\_products as select distinct p.\* from products p inner join order\_items oi on oi.order\_item\_product\_id = p.product\_id inner join orders o on o.order\_id = oi.order\_item\_order\_id inner join top\_cust tc on o.order\_customer\_id = tc.customer\_id where p.product\_price \&lt; 100&quot;);
